summary: This document is a court filing from the Ghislaine Maxwell criminal case, listing juror numbers for peremptory strikes scheduled for November 29, 2021. It provides a procedural record of the jury selection process in her trial.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: The defendant in the criminal case referenced in the court document heading.

events.title: Jury Selection for Peremptory Strikes
events.description: The court scheduled the exercise of peremptory strikes in the Ghislaine Maxwell trial, with 58 total jurors listed across two courtrooms.

locations: UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT SOUTHERN DISTRICT OF NEW YORK
keyFacts: The document is part of the criminal case against Ghislaine Maxwell (20-CR-330).
Jury selection was ongoing on November 29, 2021, with peremptory strikes scheduled.
A total of 58 jurors were listed for the peremptory strike process.
Jurors were divided between two courtrooms: Courtroom 506 and Courtroom 110.
The document is a procedural record of the trial's jury selection phase.
